snippet.title: Amber Heard Bantah Buang Kotoran Manusia di Kasur Johnny Depp
snippet.description:
Amber Heard Bantah Buang Kotoran Manusia di Kasur Johnny Depp.
Amber Heard membantah tuduhan Johnny Depp yang menyebut kalau mantan istrinya itu membuang feses atau kotoran manusia di kasur. Ia menuding justru Johnny yang punya lelucon jorok.
Juru bicara Amber Heard menjelaskan bahwa tuduhan kalau kliennya, atau salah satu temannya, buang hajat di ranjang mereka pada 2016 hanyalah kebohongan. Dia juga mengatakan justru aktor 'Pirates of the Carribbean' itu sendirilah pelakunya. Sebab Johnny disebut pernah bercanda ingin melakukan prank seperti itu.

"Tuduhan ini sungguh tidak benar dan dirancang cuma untuk mempermalukan Nona Heard. Sebagaimana bukti ditunjukkan di pengadilan, Tuan Depp membicarakan rencananya melakuka prank semacam itu bertahun-tahun sebelumnya dan itu termasuk dalam selera leluconnya yang jorok dan kasar," ungkapnya, seperti dikutip dari Page Six.
Pihak Amber Heard juga menuding tim kuasa hukum Johnny Depp sengaja mencari perhatian agar hal-hal seperti itu dijadikan judul halaman pertama sejumlah media. Dia mengklaim itu dilakukan untuk mengalihkan isu utama dari kasus ini yakni dugaan kekerasan dalam rumah tangga.

Sebelumnya saksi sidang tuntutan Johnny Depp terhadap tabloid Inggris The Sun --atas pemberitaan bahwa dia adalah seorang 'pemukul wanita' karena telah menonjok Amber-- menyebut Johnny Depp menemukan kotoran manusia di tempat tidurnya. Setelah menemukan feses, Johnny memutuskan untuk bercerai dari Amber Heard.
"Saya memutuskan untuk menceraikan Heard hari itu juga," tegas Johnny Depp.

Amber Heard sempat menyangkal dan menyalahkan anjing mereka bahwa itu adalah kotoran anjing. Namun faktanya adalah kotoran manusia, dan dia mengaku akan bertanggung jawab karena hal tersebut tidaklah berbahaya.

heard in court reveals that Johnny, 57, made "Amber Turd" jokes after blaming her for faeces he found in their bed the day after Amber's birthday party on April 21, 2016. ¬†He told the court that while he believes Amber, 34, was responsible for the defecation, he admitting under questioning that it could have been her "crass" friend, trans activist iO Tillett Wright. ¬†Johnny arrived at Amber's party two hours later after he got some bad news about his financial affairs from his accountants.   ¬†He also smoked some cannabis to relieve his stress. ¬†The Hollywood actor admitted that he went to bed to read a book after the other guests had left and he and Amber argued about his behaviour. ¬†Amber claimed that as the confrontation escalated, Johnny threw a magnum champagne bottle at her, shoved her to the floor several times and then left a note which read "Happy F***ing Birthday".   ¬†Johnny claimed that Amber had been "drinking heavily" and had attacked him while he had been reading in bed, alleging she punched him in the face four times before he grabbed her arms to stop her. ¬†He went on to say that the next day either Amber or one of her friends "defecated" in their bed, and he believes it was Amber as she reportedly told the building manager it was "just a harmless prank".  ¬†The dad-of-two claimed this was when he "resolved" to divorce her. ¬†Johnny denied that their small dog could have been responsible for the mess, but did admit that Amber's friend iO Tillett Wright could have been responsible. ¬†He said he could not be certain that Amber was responsible. ¬†The Pirates of the Caribbean star admitted that he laughed about the faeces the next day and made "Amber Turd" jokes.  ¬†Amber alleged that a month later, Johnny returned to their LA apartment to collect his belongings after deciding to divorce her. ¬†She claimed that another argument began during which he allegedly threw a phone. ¬†Johnny denied this, claiming he did not touch her. ¬†The trial was launched in relation to an article published in The Sun which made allegations of violence from Johnny towards Amber, something which he denies.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp's Friend Doug Stanhope Speaks Out About His Controversial Amber Heard Essay, Claims Depp
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp's friend Doug Stanhope is speaking out about the highly publicized essay he wrote accusing Amber Heard of blackmailing the actor -- and Heard's subsequent defamation suit against him. 

The comedian appeared on The Howard Stern Show Monday to promote his new book Digging Up Mother: A Love Story, but a portion of his interview with Stern focused on Stanhope's essay in defense of his friend, Depp, who the comedian wrote was "used, manipulated, set up," by Heard.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp's pal says snap of Amber Heard's red face is 'phoney baloney'
snippet.description: Johnny Depp 's libel trail was shown a snap of Amber Heard 's red face which she claims is her injury after he attacked her.  ¬†Heard alleges the Hollywood legend, 57, "threw a phone at her" and "smashed objects" during a blazing row a their penthouse in May 2016. ¬†The High Court in London was shown a snap of her alleged injuries yesterday. ¬†Depp denies claims he was physically violent towards Heard and is suing NGN over an article that appeared in The Sun in 2018 which branded him a "wife beater". ¬†Depp's lifelong friend Isaac Baruch was called to give evidence and described the photographs as "phoney baloney".  Read More Related Articles  Read More Related Articles  ¬†He said there were no signs of any marks, scratches, swelling or bruises on Heard's face after the alleged attack. ¬†He said: "In all the years I've known Mr Depp, I have never once seen him commit an act of violence." ¬†Baurch said in his witness statement: "She told me that he hit her in the face and threw a phone at her."  Read More Related Articles   ¬†Lawyers for NGN are defending their case based on Heard's 14 allegations of abuse, which include claims of bust-ups between 2013 and 2016. ¬†The actor has argued his ex-wife was abusive towards him during the marriage, which she denies. ¬†Earlier this week, Depps security guard of seven years Travis McGivern has claimed he saw Heard be physically violent towards the Hollywood actor.   Read More Related Articles   ¬†Cross examining him, Wass QC acting on behalf of The Sun said: "You are lying about your description in order to assist Mr Depp who was extremely angry and extremely violent on that occasion?" ¬†McGivern replied: "No maam. I'm not lying." ¬†Amber Heard is The Sun's star witness in the case. ¬†The case will continue next week.

snippet.title: Amber Heard 'had two black eyes' as she appeared on US show after Depp 'attack'
snippet.description: Amber Heard appeared on a US chat show with "two black eyes" the night after she was allegedly assaulted by ex-husband Johnny Depp.  ¬†The American actress claimed she was slapped and pulled up the stairs by the Pirates of the Caribbean star during a furious bust-up at their LA apartment in 2015.  Depp, 57, has admitted to headbutting his former spouse at their penthouse but claimed it was "accidental" when he took to the stand at the High Court.  The court was told today how Heard, 34, appeared on James Corden's Late Late Show the night after the alleged incident on December 16 2015.  Heard allegedly told her stylist Samantha McMillen after her television appearance: "Can you believe I just did that show with two black eyes?"  Read More Related Articles  Read More Related Articles  ¬† The Hollywood stylist took to the stand today in the libel case, claiming she had not seen Heard with any visible marks on her body or face.  In a witness statement to the court, Ms McMillen said: "I saw her throughout the day, in good light, at close range, wearing no makeup.  "Throughout the day, I could see clearly that Amber did not have any visible marks, bruises, cuts, or injuries to her face or any other part of her body.  "After the show, Ms Heard said to me, 'Can you believe I just did that show with two black eyes?' But she did not have any black eyes, and had been visibly uninjured throughout the day and at that moment.  Read More Related Articles  Read More Related Articles  ¬†"I later learned that Ms Heard had accused Johnny Depp of violently abusing her the previous night."  Ms McMillen said that she had been "confused" by the actress' comments about the bruises saying: "I didn't see the black eyes, but also I don't want to, you know, raise any sort of ‚Äì I just wanted to go home."  The stylist said she later overheard Heard tell a friend: "Make sure to get those pictures on to my computer," but she did not know what images the actress was referring to.  Sasha Wass QC, representing News Group Newspapers, later referred to a message sent by Heard in December 2015 which read: "Johnny did a number on me last night."  ¬†"Did Ms Heard ever say to you that Johnny 'did a number on her?'," the barrister asked Ms McMillen. snippet.title: Johnny Depp trial shown poo on bed that 'destroyed' actor's marriage to actress
snippet.description: Photographs were shown in London's High Court today of the poo, which reportedly "destroyed" Amber Heard and Johnny Depp's marriage. ¬†Depp, 57, had accused Heard of pooing in their marital bed, which he said was the final alleged incident that gave him the resolve to break up with her. ¬†Heard, 34, released a statement denying she was responsible for the stool found by Depp's cleaner beneath a top sheet in a bed in the Los Angeles penthouse apartment they shared the morning after the actress's 30th birthday. ¬†She appeared to point the finger at the Pirates Of The Caribbean star. ¬†Depp had walked out the night before after a bust-up when he was late for a dinner party Heard was hosting for 12 pals.  Read More Related Articles  Read More Related Articles  ¬†The Hollywood A-lister admitted swapping messages with one of his staff about the mystery deposit in which they joked about "Amber Turd" and "Amber in the dumps". ¬†But Depp told the High Court in London the act was "one of the most absurd unexpected statements" he had ever witnessed and effectively ended their marriage. ¬†Sasha Wass QC, representing News Group Newspapers who Depp is suing for libel, suggested his pet Teacup Yorkshire Terrier Boo was the true culprit.  ¬†The pint-sized pooch had suffered bowel problems after eating a ball of the actor's cannabis. ¬†But Depp told the High Court in London: "It was a mystery grumpy, if you will, left in the bed. It was not left by a 3lb or 4lb dog. ¬†"I was convinced that it was either Miss Heard herself or one of her cohorts involved in leaving human faeces on the bed."  ¬†Depp said he suspected it could also have been Heard's US photographer and TV host pal Tillett Wright who had been at the dinner party and was "crass enough to commit such an act". ¬†Depp's housekeeper Hilda Vargas, who gave testimony today said she was "horrified and disgusted" when she found the stool. ¬†She said she knew it was ‚Äúhuman‚Äù, took photos and sent them to one of Depp's staff. ¬†Giving evidence via videolink from Beverly Hills, through a Spanish interpreter, she said she knew neither Boo ‚Äì nor Heard's miniature dog Pistol ‚Äì were responsible because they could not climb on the bed by themselves and the turd was "too large". ¬†She said leaving her to scoop the poop signalled a "lack of respect". ¬†After cleaning it up Hilda moved to Depp's house in West Hollywood to start work there when Heard suddenly arrived.  ¬†She said: "Miss Heard then called me over to talk to her in the living room. ¬†"She told me that the pictures I had taken of the faeces had destroyed her marriage. ¬†"I was very nervous and so I apologised, even though I did not believe that their marital problems were my fault or that I had done anything wrong. ¬†"I also told Miss Heard that the faeces were there, that there was nothing I could do. ¬†"Miss Heard argued with me saying there were no faeces in the bed." ¬†Vargas continued: "I, again, said the faeces were there, that they were large and smelled awful.  ¬†"Miss He

snippet.title: Johnny Depp gave daughter cannabis at 13 claiming it was 'responsible parenting'
snippet.description: Johnny Depp and his ex-wife Amber Heard appeared at the Royal Courts of Justice in London today for the start of his libel case.  ¬†During the trial, the 57-year-old was asked about his past drug use as well as some violent incidents. ¬†He said that he was introduced to drugs when he was a child and gave his daughter Lily-Rose cannabis when she was 13. ¬†The Hollywood actor said that he gave his daughter the drug as he wanted her to have a safe experience with it. ¬†The Fantastic Beasts star claimed he believed that it was "responsible parenting" allowing Lily-Rose to try the drug.  Read More Related Articles  Read More Related Articles  ¬†He said that he did not want her having a bad experience with it when he was not around. ¬†Earlier in the trial, the Disney star said that he'd first taken drugs at 11 when he took one of his mother's nerve pills. ¬†He claimed that he had taken "every kind of drug there was" by the time he turned 14. ¬†Depp told the court that they were an escape from "a lot of upheaval" and "pain" from his childhood.  Read More Related Articles  Read More Related Articles  ¬†He admitted to using cocaine, ecstasy, LSD "when I was younger", mushrooms and cannabis. ¬†But he denied ever taking ketamine. ¬†Depp claimed that many of the figures he admired had taken drugs, including American writer Hunter S Thompson. ¬†He said he had taken drugs twice with musician Marilyn Manson "many years ago". ¬†And he spoke of taking drugs with British actor Paul Bettany when the barrister used the phrase "drug buddies".  ¬†Depp said: "Paul Bettany is an actor that I've worked with several times, he is a friend and we have... yes, we have dabbled in drugs together." ¬†He listed cocaine, alcohol, Xanax and Adderall as some of the drugs they had taken. ¬†The libel case concerns an April 2018 column in The Sun, which spoke of allegations of violence against Heard by Depp. ¬†Depp denies ever having been violent towards his ex-wife. ¬†He will continue giving evidence tomorrow (Wednesday).

snippet.description: Johnny Depp 's court case continued today at London's High Court as he arrived at his third day of giving evidence in his libel trial against News Group Newspapers over a story published in The Sun in 2018.  ¬†In the story, the Pirates of the Caribbean star was labelled a "wife beater" in the publication's headline - which he strongly denies. ¬†During today's appearance, Depp told the court how he used his mangled finger to write a message in blood after severing the top of his finger so the bone could be seen during a row with his ex-wife Amber Heard, who The Sun alleged he was violent towards. ¬†The A-List actor, 47, recalled the story after Sasha Wass QC, for NGN, asked Depp about an argument he had with ex-wife Heard during a 2015 trip to Australia, where he was filming a Pirates Of The Caribbean movie.   ¬†The courtroom heard how the couple, who wed in 2015 and divorced in 2017, ended up erupting into a heated row at the house they were renting at the time. ¬†During which, Depp suffered a severed finger and was left "feeling upset" as he admitted to then using the blood soaked stump to write a chilling note on the mirror in the bathroom. ¬†Ms Wass told the court: "These [pictures] are of the house - you had written on a mirror. You had dipped your injured finger in paint to write the graffiti."   ¬†Depp than clarified that the message was written in his own blood, adding: "Yes I started using the blood from my finger... ¬†Using his own blood as well as paint and lipstick the court heard how Depp scrawled messages on a mirror, a wall and a lampshade. ¬†Ms Wass asked: "Why did you feel it okay to paint graffiti all over the house all over the house, which was not your house. Which must have taken a long time."   ¬†Depp replied: "It didn‚Äôt take that long - help and security arrived." ¬†In the photos one of the messages read "Good luck", Depp explained he wrote it because he felt their relationship was over. ¬†He then said he "went into some kind of breakdown.'' ¬†Lawyer Ms Wass claimed the actor had lost the tip of his finger while smashing a plastic phone against a wall repeatedly while arguing with Heard. ¬†Depp denied this version of events, telling the court: "I didn't spend much time on the phone."   ¬†He has previously alleged his finger was injured after his former wife threw a glass vodka bottle at him during the row. ¬†During today's testimony, Depp said of the injury: "I had just lost the tip of my finger and as a musician it‚Äôs a little upsetting when you see the bone sticking out." ¬†Ms Wass said Ms Heard came downstairs to find him nursing the injury and denies she was present when it happened. ¬†A picture of Depp being treated for the injury while laying on his back in a hospital bed had previously been presented to court during the opening statements.   ¬†The actor, who was filming as his character Jack Sparrow at the time for the Disney pirate franchise, went on to claim that as he was due at work the next day for filming he told the production c
